HEADWORD: Drongo
<hw>Dron"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Drongos</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
passerine bird of the family <fam>Dicrurid⟦ae⟧</fam>. They are usually
black with a deeply forked tail. They are natives of Asia, Africa, and
Australia; -- called also <altname>drongo shrikes</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
